"<article>
    

    <p>
      Machine learning models require careful feature engineering to achieve good performance.
      The quality of features directly impacts model accuracy.
    </p>

    
      <h2>Validation Methods</h2>

      <p>
        Cross-validation helps prevent overfitting by testing the model on multiple data splits.
        K-fold cross-validation is the most common approach.
      </p>

      <pre><code data-lang="python">from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score
scores = cross_val_score(model, X, y, cv=5)</code></pre>

      <p>
        Gradient descent converges to a local minimum when the learning rate is properly tuned.
        Adaptive methods like Adam adjust the rate automatically.
      </p>

      <p><img src="https://example.com/images/gradient.png" alt="Gradient Descent" width="800" height="400">
    </p>

    <svg viewBox="0 0 100 100" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" data-chart="loss">
